         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... 2. Thereupon father [and] mother of the Bodhisattva ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1952"/><citedRange>21</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... just like the one (?) (has (?)) the desire for dear life ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (|| In the ?-)tune: || For great wishes, without moderation ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... like (a father). Without looking at all the Saṃsāra-beings ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... to be separated from (me). 1. Thereupon Mūkaphalgu, the Bodhisattva, (speaks (?)) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [ye] lords, even without my leaving the house ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... he thought: this one [i.e. the son] speaks according to will [and] sensitivity, but not ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>300</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>144</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>205</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... for seven days he did not eat [and] he did not drink. || In the P.-tune: || ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... abjuring from food out of desire for virtue, the compassionate one ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having recognized the Bodhisattva as one [about] to renounce [his] life, (through) suffering (?) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (?) to cause; not, however, ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (|| In the ?-)tune : || Hard [it is] to practice the penitence of the penitent ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="philcomment">The translation is largely based on <bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1952"/><citedRange>21-22</citedRange></bibl>, and <bibl><title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/></bibl>.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment">This line begins with the name of a tune of perhaps 4x18 syllables, rhythm 7/7/4.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment">The tune seems to have 4x12 syllables, rhythm 5/7.</note><note corresp="#b6" type="philcomment">This line begins with the name of a tune of perhaps 4x25 syllables, rhythm 5/5/8/7.</note></p>
         </div>
